        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 3:18AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 315 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms across Menard and northern Mason Counties, moving
south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mason, Menard, Art, Loyal Valley, Yates Crossing, Saline, Streeter,
Camp Air, Hilda, Grit, Katemcy, Pontotoc, Hedwigs Hill, Long
Mountain, London, Hext, Fort Mckavett, and Camp Sol Maye.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 447 and 455.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
